$interpreted: Theodore: ... So that's it for the nobles who defected to Angelia's side? A lot fewer than I thought.
Secretary: Yes, your Majesty. King Theodore's rule has been brilliant. It's no surprise that the nobles know which side they should be on.

Theodore: How about the movement of the desert lizards? 
At a time like this, we must pay even more attention to those damn reptiles...
Soldier: King Theodore!
Soldier: Your Majesty, we received a message from the Bears.
Theodore: ... Speak.
Soldier: Bears' message. They say they've captured traitor Angelia and have forced Dylan and Sunshine Infantry to surrender.
Soldier: Now, they want your Majesty to... honor your promises...

Theodore: Muhahahahahaha....
... This day has come much sooner than I ever imagined!
Secretary: King Theodore, what would you like me to do?

Theodore: Here's a list of presents that I agreed to gift to the Bears. Prepare them as soon as possible. 
Don't slack off, they are precious guests.
Secretary: Understood.
Theodore: As for this one, you take this to...

Theodore: You must be Chieftain Crushfang of the Bears, yes? 
Come to think of it, this is our first official meeting.
Crushfang: Quit the chattering. Not here to have friendly chat with you.
Angelia: Theodore! Didn't imagine that you would settle for such dirty tricks...
Theodore: For the future of Kingdom of the Sun, this is just a necessary measure; and you, will be the cornerstone of our new friendship with the Bears.

Crushfang: No interest in your family bickering. 
Show me what you promised.
Theodore: All the presents and resources are right here. Most importantly...
Theodore: The "Permanent Non-aggression Pact", signed personally by me. On top of it all, I must return it to you in person under the eyewitness of everyone.
Theodore: Chieftain Crushfang, you're quite the thoughtful fellow.
Crushfang: To prevent the king from breaking his own promise, this is just a necessary insurance.
Theodore: Wait, something's not right!
Angelia: Take down Theodore!
Crushfang: Your head's alright?
Dagger: You stinkin old man, if all that was just for a show, then tell me beforehand!
Crushfang: According to Hyde, to make sure we fool Theodore, it's best that I be the only bear that knows.

Furygrowl: ... Never knew it's strategy too, until right before we departed for here...
... I even spoke ill of the princess, how dare I...
Dagger: Whatever, victory is in sight. Angelia won't make fuss over that!
Theodore: ......
